data.name: Korean BBQ Burger
data.quickTastyDescription: A juicy burger infused with Korean flavors, topped with a spicy kimchi slaw and a sweet soy glaze.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, mix ground beef with soy sauce, brown sugar, garlic powder, ginger powder, and black pepper until well combined.
Form the mixture into 4 equal patties.
Preheat a grill or skillet over medium-high heat and cook the patties for about 4-5 minutes per side or until desired doneness.
In a separate bowl, mix kimchi with chopped green onions and set aside.
Toast the burger buns on the grill or in a toaster until lightly golden.
Assemble the burgers by placing a patty on each bun, topping with kimchi slaw, and drizzling with sesame oil and sesame seeds. Serve immediately.
data.detailedName: Korean BBQ Burger with Kimchi Slaw
data.modifiersForBase: Korean flavors with kimchi and soy glaze
